The paper deals with knowledge extraction from databases and data mining, which are core topics in the database (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel framework that integrates utility theory, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the analysis of sequential data, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
